    <section class="section">
      <p class="eyebrow">Learn</p>
      <h2 class="display section-title">Paint types, finishes &amp; how to use them</h2>
      <p class="section-sub">A quick guide before you buy — what each paint type is for, and where it works best.</p>

      <div class="learn-grid">
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Emulsion (water-based)</h3>
          <p>Water-thinned paint for interior and exterior walls. Low odour, quick-drying, easy to clean up with water. Best for walls, ceilings and plaster.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Enamel / gloss (oil-based)</h3>
          <p>Solvent-thinned paint with a hard, shiny, washable finish. Best for wood, metal, doors, window frames and areas that need frequent wiping down.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Matt finish</h3>
          <p>Flat, non-reflective look that hides surface imperfections well. Great for ceilings and living spaces with lower traffic.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Silk / satin finish</h3>
          <p>A soft sheen with better wipe-clean resistance than matt. Suited to kitchens, hallways, and family areas.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Gloss finish</h3>
          <p>Highly reflective and the most durable, scrubbable finish. Ideal for doors, skirting, railings and metalwork.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Weathershield (exterior)</h3>
          <p>Formulated to withstand rain, UV and temperature swings. Use on external walls, facades and render.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Primers &amp; undercoats</h3>
          <p>Applied first on new or bare surfaces to improve adhesion and even out porosity before the topcoat goes on.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card learn-card">
          <h3 class="display">Thinners &amp; solvents</h3>
          <p>Used to adjust paint consistency for spraying or brushing, and to clean equipment. Match the thinner to the paint type — oil-based paints need oil-based thinners.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
